# Dependency Governance

## Must
- Pin dependency versions and record source, purpose, and update cadence.
- Route third-party usage through project wrappers/facades in core modules.
- Track dependency license and compatibility status before adoption.
- Require changelog review for dependency updates that affect determinism/perf/ABI.

## Must Not
- Do not call third-party APIs directly from critical core paths without a boundary layer.
- Do not merge unpinned or floating dependency references in governed targets.

## Required Evidence
- Dependency intake note with risk summary and owner (`self`).
- Wrapper boundary reference for each new core dependency.
